advisories.title: Bootstrap vulnerable to Cross-Site Scripting (XSS)
advisories.description: In Bootstrap starting in version 2.3.0 and prior to 3.4.0, as well as 4.x before 4.1.2, XSS is possible in the collapse data-parent attribute.

advisories.title: Bootstrap Cross-site Scripting vulnerability
advisories.description:
In Bootstrap 2.x from 2.0.4, 3.x before 3.4.0 and 4.x-beta before 4.0.0-beta.2, XSS is possible in the data-target attribute. Note that this is a different vulnerability than CVE-2018-14041.

See https://blog.getbootstrap.com/2018/12/13/bootstrap-3-4-0/ for more info.

advisories.title: Bootstrap Cross-site Scripting vulnerability
advisories.description: In Bootstrap starting in version 2.3.0 and prior to versions 3.4.0 and 4.1.2, XSS is possible in the data-container property of tooltip.  This is similar to CVE-2018-14041.

advisories.title: Bootstrap Cross-site Scripting vulnerability
advisories.description: In Bootstrap 4.x before 4.1.2, XSS is possible in the data-target property of scrollspy. This is similar to CVE-2018-14042.

advisories.title: Bootstrap Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) vulnerability
advisories.description: A vulnerability has been identified in Bootstrap that exposes users to Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) attacks. The issue is present in the carousel component, where the data-slide and data-slide-to attributes can be exploited through the href attribute of an <a> tag due to inadequate sanitization. This vulnerability could potentially enable attackers to execute arbitrary JavaScript within the victim's browser.

advisories.title: Bootstrap Vulnerable to Cross-Site Scripting
advisories.description:
Versions of `bootstrap` prior to 3.4.1 for 3.x and 4.3.1 for 4.x are vulnerable to Cross-Site Scripting (XSS). The  `data-template` attribute of the tooltip and popover plugins lacks input sanitization and may allow attacker to execute arbitrary JavaScript.


## Recommendation

For `bootstrap` 4.x upgrade to 4.3.1 or later.
For `bootstrap` 3.x upgrade to 3.4.1 or later.
